<DOCNO> NYT19990322.0094 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-22 10:28 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A9309 &Cx1f; tad-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TECH-KIDS23-COX     03-22 0411
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TECH-KIDS23-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    `Rugrats' a fun way to teach use of PC
 &HT;    By Yusuf Davis
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The ``Rugrats Adventure Game'' is a fun, interactive way to
introduce children to the computer.
</P>
<P>
   Modeled after the popular TV show and full-length feature film,
the ``Rugrats'' program is easy to use for kids with little or no
computer experience. Multilevel challenges keep the adventure fun
for kids of
</P>
<P>
   different ages and abilities.
</P>
<P>
   With more than 30 puzzles and games embedded in an entertaining
story, the adventure game is a hands-on method to help teach logic
and problem-solving to kids ages 6 to 10.
</P>
<P>
   Bobby Johnson of southeast Atlanta, who is just learning to use
a computer, wasn't interested in the educational value of
``Rugrats''; he just wanted to have some fun.
</P>
<P>
   ``This game is cool,'' said the 7-year-old computer novice, who
uses the program for hours at a time. ``I could do this all day.''
</P>
<P>
   The Rugrats are a group of diaper-clad toddlers who talk and act
like babies in the presence of grown-ups, but when the adults are
gone, the babies talk and act like big kids and get into big
trouble.
</P>
<P>
   By clicking on the characters and objects in their 3-D world,
Bobby uses the mouse to control the actions and words of Tommy,
Chuckie, Phil, Lil and Anglica, as he guides them through their
adventure.
</P>
<P>
   Their mission is to rescue Reptar, the toy dinosaur, from the
jaws of Hubert the Trash Monster, so that Reptar can save the
planet from alien invaders.
</P>
<P>
   At first, navigating the adventure was a little difficult for
Bobby. Sometimes he got stuck and frustrated. By himself, he
couldn't figure out what to do. But after a little instruction, he
learned that he could get help by clicking on one of the Rugrats.
After that, Bobby was off and running.
</P>
<P>
   One of the program's most useful features is ``game-save,''
which allows kids to stop the adventure at any point, then pick up
later where they left off.
</P>
<P>
   Overall, ``Rugrats'' was a big hit with Bobby, who said he was
going to stay with the program until he helped the babies save the
Earth.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is the bestest game I've ever played,'' Bobby said,
imitating the voice and baby talk of Tommy, the Rugrats' 1-year-old
leader.
</P>
<P>
   `RUGRATS ADVENTURE GAME'
</P>
<P>
   Developer: Broderbund
</P>
<P>
   Price: $29.95
</P>
<P>
   Format: PC and Macintosh
</P>
<P>
   Bobby's grade: A+
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-22-99 1028EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
