 &HT;    NEWS FOR KIDS: Buddy, Socks show their home
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Take an online tour of the White House at http://www
</P>
<P>
   .whitehouse.gov/WH/kids/html/kidshome.html.
</P>
<P>
   Hosted by Socks the cat and Buddy the dog, the tour includes
tales about the kids and pets who've lived there.
</P>
<P>
   You can also send e-mail to the president, vice president and
their wives. They'll respond by regular mail.
</P>
<P>
   Disney asks for favorite teachers
</P>
<P>
   Do you have favorite teachers? Well, Disney wants you to
nominate them for the 10th Disney American Teacher Awards. You have
until March 31 to call toll-free 1-877-ATA-TEACH or log onto
http://www.disneylearning.org to put them up for the award.
Nominated teachers will receive a contest application. Teachers can
win up to $25,000 if they're chosen in November.
</P>
<P>
   Did you know?
</P>
<P>
   Holy anaconda! The average human has 696 muscles, while a single
caterpillar has more than 4,000. Animal lovers can gobble up lots
more knowledge on some 100 creatures in ``Animalogy: Weird and
Wacky Animal Facts'' by Rita Thievon Mullin, illustrated by Anders
Wenngren (Discovery Channel/Crown, $9.99). This 64-page info feast
also includes lots of awesome close-up photographs.
</P>
