r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BOOK-REVIEW-TEXAS-HNS     03-22 0311
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BOOK-REVIEW-TEXAS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LONE STAR SPRING ARRIVES IN A COLORFUL NEW BOOK 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By JUDYTH RIGLER  
 c.1999 San Antonio Express-News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Spring is here, and what better time to consider a new and
heartwarming book about the season.
</P>
<P>
   The spirit of ``Heralds of Spring in Texas'' by naturalist
Roland H. Wauer (Texas A&AMP;M University Press, $24.95) can best be
captured in the author's story about his yearly anticipation of the
return of the buff-bellied hummingbird to the back yard of his home
in the south Texas city of Victoria.
</P>
<P>
   ``One day it is not present, and the very next it is sipping
sugar water from one of the feeders as if it had never left,''
Wauer writes. ```Betty, our buff-belly is back!' I yell to my wife.
She, too, must have a look. And we admire our new, eagerly
anticipated neighbor almost as if it were a newly born human
child.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Heralds of Spring in Texas'' divides the state into seven
regions and describes the harbingers of the season in each. For the
Hill Country, there's the bluebonnet, of course, as well as the
redbud trees, the mountain laurel, the chimney swifts, field
sparrows and other annual visitors _ even Maury Maverick's beloved
purple martins.
</P>
<P>
   If you grew up anywhere in Texas, this book will bring back
plenty of springtime memories, sights and smells.
</P>
<P>
   Quotes from Texans and visitors enhance chapters, and line
drawings by Ralph Scott add a lot to this volume in the Louise
Lindsey Merrick natural environment series of A&AMP;M Press.
</P>
<P>
   The late J. Frank Dobie, Texas' folktale king and lover of
nature, said of the Texas bluebonnet: ``No other flower _ for me at
least _ brings such upsurging of the spirit and at the same time
such restfulness.'' And A.L. Morgan described bluebonnet time as
the time ``when the sky falls on Texas.'' Amen.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
