<P>
   WASHINGTON/POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-STAKE _ WASHINGTON - (For use in event of bombing by
NATO). What's at stake for the United States? Developing. (Deans,
Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   NARAL _ WASHINGTON _ A leading abortion rights group began
airing TV ads Monday in Iowa and New Hampshire accusing George Bush
and Elizabeth Dole of covering up their strong anti-abortion views
to attract moderate voters. Includes material from an interview
with Kate Michelman, head of the National Abortion and Reproductive
Rights Action League. (Shepard 450).
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (p) politics categories.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-FRAUD _ WASHINGTON _ A Senate subcommittee begins two
days of hearings on Internet securities fraud and how consumers can
protect themselves. (Glass, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   NURSING-HOMES _ WASHINGTON _ The Senate Special Aging Committee
holds a hearing on a General Accounting Office complaints about
nursing home care from residents, their family members or nursing
home employees. (Schultz, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOL-FUNDING _ WASHINGTON - Congress on Monday begins debate
on the budget, with Democrats and Republicans each claiming to
favor more spending than the other on elementary and secondary
education. But many of their differences are built on clever
arithmetic, rather than the actual amount of money that would reach
real schools in the real world. (Mollison, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOL-DATA, comparing education spending plans of President
Clinton, Senate Budget Committee and House Budget Committee.
</P>
<P>
   TAX-CORDES _ WASHINGTON _ An Austin businessman faces a $3.5
million federal tax bill related to a business he says he doesn't
own. John J. Cordes, a construction consultant, and his wife, Sue,
have filed a petition asking the U.S. Tax Court here to overturn an
Internal Revenue Service ruling that he received $6.96 million in
benefits from the Cordes Jeep-Eagle dealership owned by his father
in Lawton, Okla. (Moskal, Cox News Service)
</P>
