<HEADLINE>
`PLEASANTVILLE' PLEASANT `JOE' NO LONGER MIGHTY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Pleasantville'' _ Time travel meets retro-pop
culture in the story of two '90s teenagers going back to the '50s
and shaking things up. Appealing as a demonstration of filmmaking
technique, and pleasantly surprising as a whole.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mighty Joe Young'' _ Joe mighty old. Disney exhumes the great
ape, with dismal results. The 1949 version, a rip-off of ``King
Kong,'' looks great by comparison. At least it had terrific special
effects by master Ray Harryhausen.
</P>
<P>
   ``Bride of Chucky'' _ The nasty little doll needs a life
partner, so he gets one in a bloody sendup of ``Bride of
Frankenstein.'' It's not saying much, but this is the best of the
Chuckys.
</P>
<P>
   ``Jerry Springer's Ringmaster'' _ Springer's three-ring TV
circus brought lifelessly to the movies. Maybe Cincinnati should
just reelect him mayor. He'd do less damage.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DVD UPDATE: Fox Lorber is preparing a half-dozen of Francois
Truffaut's titles for release in late April. Films include ``The
400 Blows,'' ``The Last Metro,'' ``Confidentially Yours,'' ``Love
on the Run,'' ``Shoot the Piano Player,'' and ``Two English
Girls.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The ``Facets Complete Video Catalogue Number 15,'' a listing of
more than 35,000 titles available on VHS, DVD, and laserdisc, is on
sale for $9.95. In addition to the wide-ranging selections _ from
obscure short subjects to out-of-print titles _ the 650-page book
is a great reference. Order at 800-331-6197.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: March 30: ``The Rugrats Movie,''
``Oblomov,'' ``Siberiade,'' ``Home Fries,'' ``Mutual Needs.'' April
6: ``Beloved,'' ``American History X,'' ``A Soldier's Daughter
Never Cries,'' ``I Still Know What You Did Last Summer,'' ``Franz
Kafka's It's a Wonderful Life,'' ``An Unexpected Life,'' ``Meet Joe
Black,'' ``Legalese,'' ``The Dentist 2.'' April 13: ``Basil,''
``One Tough Cop,'' ``The Fury Within,'' ``Detroit 9000,''
``Scooby-Doo's Greatest Mysteries,'' ``Conspirators of Pleasure.''
April 20: ``A Bug's Life,'' ``Monument Ave.,'' ``Simon Birch,''
``Corporate Ladder,'' ``Kissed,'' ``Apt Pupil,'' ``A Night at the
Roxbury.'' April 27: ``Elizabeth,'' ``Ten Benny,'' ``Stepmom,''
``Happiness,'' ``Ground Control,'' ``Future Fantastic,'' ``At First
Sight.'' May 4: ``Babe: Pig in the City,'' ``You've Got Mail,''
``Frank Sinatra: The Best Is Yet to Come.'' May 11: ``Another Day
in Paradise,'' ``Velvet Goldmine.'' May 18: ``Holy Man,'' ``Rowing
With the Wind.''
</P>
</TEXT>
