</P>
<P>
   The 13-year-old son of a playwright friend of ours just got into
the Stuyvesant High School class of 2003, one of about 700 accepted
from among approximately 20,000 applicants.
</P>
<P>
   Shortly after he received the good news, he was on a bus with
his father and confessed that he had really prayed a lot, asking
God to get him into Stuyvesant. However, he added, now that he had
been accepted he wished that hadn't prayed quite so much, because
now he'll never really know if he got in on his own merit or if
only because God pulled strings for him.
</P>
<P>
   Tom Collimore was recently in Vermont where, he says, New York's
reputation is ``inexplicably mixed.'' He was given change in one of
the rural general stores for a new $20 bill and realized the
cashier had taken it for a $100 bill. He returned the extra money
and, bearing his city's reputation in mind, said: ``Remember this
moment. I AM FROM NEW YORK.''
</P>
<P>
   I was recently walking near Times Square after a matinee and
dropped an earring, which fell through a sidewalk grating in front
of a hotel. The doorman saw what happened but told us the grate
belonged to Con Edison and the hotel had no access to it.
</P>
<P>
   The earring had been a gift from my husband, so I decided to try
my luck with the utility company. On Monday morning, I telephoned,
finally reached a live person and explained what had happened. On
Tuesday morning, the phone rang: It was the chief of the emergency
crew and he had my earring. So much for impersonal giant
corporations!
</P>
<P>
   _ SARI REIFBERG
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S `LATE NIGHT WITH CONAN O'BRIEN' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Mayor Giuliani said that he watched the heavyweight fight on
pay-per-view and he said that the decision was `a travesty.'
Giuliani is also upset because both boxers were topless.''
</P>
<P>
   ``There's a Web site on the Internet that's showing nude
pictures of Keith Richards. The Web site is at
www.loseyourappetite.com.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Dennis Rodman hasn't shown up to play with the Lakers since
Saturday because he says he has some personal issues to deal with.
Apparently it's a tough time for Rodman because he's going through
menopause.''
</P>
<P>
   ``This week Paula Jones announced that she and her husband are
getting separated, but she said things aren't going to get ugly.
Jones said, `We're just separating; it's not like I'm getting my
old nose back.'''  &QL; 
``The St. Patrick's Day parade was held in New York today and this
was the ninth year in a row that the Irish Gay and Lesbian
Organization was banned from marching. On the bright side, they
were invited to a huge keg party at Tinky Winky's.''
</P>
<P>
   ``During a prison brawl this week, Charles Manson had his guitar
smashed. As a result, Manson said he's going to form an a cappella
group with the voices in his head.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Yesterday, the Vatican released a new CD where Pope John Paul
II recites prayers while classical and rock music play underneath.
I think the Pope is taking this thing a bit too far because today
he announced he's having a feud with West Coast rappers.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Yesterday, a federal advisory board said that marijuana is not
a gateway to the use of harder drugs. However, they said that
marijuana is a gateway to spending an entire afternoon watching the
Cartoon Network.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Yesterday in Iowa several Amish teens rioted and were arrested
for vandalizing a farm and overturning several buggies. The worst
part is the teens spray-painted everything with the words,
`Electricity Rules.'''
</P>
<P>
   nn
</P>
<P>
   ``The winners of the Oscars have already been decided, but only
two people know who they are. Apparently the entertainment industry
is a bit suspicious because one of those people is Don King.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Fashion executives say that only a few of the actresses
actually return the expensive gowns lent to them by top designers.
Apparently the rest of them sell their gowns to Dennis Rodman.''
</P>
<P>
   ``According to a brand new book about celebrity pets Oprah
Winfrey has been having trouble controlling her dog. Apparently,
Oprah can get her dog to sit and roll over but he still won't read
any of the books she recommends.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The other day on `60 Minutes' Mike Wallace showed an old
interview he did with Oprah Winfrey 13 years ago where Oprah looks
overweight and unpolished. Of course, it was 13 years ago so
Wallace looked old and wrinkled.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S `THE TONIGHT SHOW WITH JAY LENO' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``The big story this week -- they've been conducting marijuana
research all over the country, or as it's normally called, spring
break.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Congress wants to give itself an increase of $5,000 a year.
That's just jealousy. They saw how much Clinton and Gore were
getting from the Chinese, and now they want a raise too.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Al Gore opened his presidential campaign in Iowa by talking
about how as a young man, he slopped the hogs. Isn't that how
Clinton got in trouble?''
</P>
<P>
   ``Some exciting news: after 40 years Monopoly is introducing a
new game piece. It's a little bag of money and it's an exact
replica of the one Don King gave each of the judges.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Researchers at Cornell University say studies prove that
parents do in fact have a favorite child. I think Woody Allen
proved that.''
</P>
<P>
   ``St. Patrick's Day, the biggest day of the year for Irish
politicians. Did you see the hot thing in Washington now? This is
the button they're all wearing: `Lewinsky me, I'm Irish.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``They've decided they're already going to have a rematch of the
Holyfield/Lewis fight. I hope they don't make the same mistake they
made last time, hiring those NFL referees to judge.''
</P>
<P>
   ``McDonalds is now introducing a new hamburger with four
patties: 790 calories and 41 grams of fat. I believe it's called
the McTripp.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It happened again. A Los Angeles High School teacher has been
arrested for having sex with one of her students. No wonder Clinton
wants to hire 100,000 more teachers.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM `WEEKEND UPDATE' ON NBC's `SATURDAY NIGHT LIVE' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``This week Paula Jones announced that she and her husband are
separating. One of their disagreements has been over how to spend
the money Jones received in her settlement with President Clinton.
She wants to spend it on clothing and jewelry, and he wants a new
set of tires for the house.''
</P>
<P>
   ``In an interview published this week in the British newspaper
`Express,' Monica Lewinsky said she was upset that people seemed to
believe her relationship with President Clinton was a one-way
affair. Hey Monica, you performed oral sex on him and then he ate a
pizza. That's a one-way affair.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The Energy Department is asking the Senate this week for an $8
million budget increase to beef up security at U.S. nuclear
laboratories. Security at one of the labs was so lax, a group of
hip-looking teenagers was able to slip past guards by flashing a
pack of Mentos.''
</P>
<P>
   ``At court martial proceedings this week, Major General David
Hale was ordered to pay $22,000 for committing adultery with the
wives of four of his subordinates. That's only $5,000 a piece. If
Paula Jones is worth $850,000, what do these ladies look like?''
</P>
<P>
   ``White House drug czar Barry McCaffrey said Wednesday that
despite new reports about the benefits of smoking marijuana, it is
still an illegal drug and would remain so. After the announcement,
McCaffrey drove off in his limited edition Marlboro truck.''
</P>
<P>
   ``A group of travel journalists have voted Niagara Falls as the
best location to celebrate the millennium. The worst location:
Sitting between David Arquette and Robin Williams at Howie Mandel's
New Year's party.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Let me tell you how crooked boxing is: Last night, HBO
replayed the Evander Holyfield-Lennox Lewis fight. Holyfield
knocked him out in the fourth.''
</P>
<P>
   ``During an international tournament in Manhattan this week,
Maurice Ashley has become the first African-American chess
grandmaster in history, proving once again that blacks are just
better athletes.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Before their game on Tuesday, the New Jersey Nets got a pep
talk from motivational speaker Tony Robbins. The Nets lost anyway,
and Robbins was immediately traded to Milwaukee for Deepak
Chopra.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The former president of Ecuador was jailed this week on
corruption charges that claim he inflated the Ecuadorian payroll
with over 1,000 phantom employees. He will be extradited to New
York where he will immediately be made shop steward at the Javit's
Center.''
</P>
<P>
   ``This week Britain granted citizenship to residents of its
overseas territories including, Bermuda, and the British Virgin
Islands. The happy new citizens then went back to their life of
standing outside a barbed wire fence watching people at Club Med do
Jell-O shots.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Floyd Hooker, an Oswego Hotel janitor, won $45 million in the
New York State Lottery this week and said that it is probably the
greatest thing that has ever happened to him. Really, are you sure
you want to step out on a limb like that? I thought the best thing
in your life was the time you got the drumstick at the Salvation
Army Thanksgiving dinner.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Sony Records and the Vatican have joined forces and are
releasing `Abba Pater' a CD-ROM and music video featuring Pope John
Paul reciting psalms and singing. The high point of the video is
when the Pope tears up a picture of Sinead O'Connor.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Four Amish teens were arrested this week for smashing 44
windows and overturning buggies during a rampage at the home of an
Amish farmer. The boys were easily captured by police because they
move like molasses.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Marilyn Manson canceled some shows this week after twisting
his ankle. Apparently, the antichrist doesn't have as high
threshold of pain as you might think.''
</P>
<P>
   ``A judge this week threw out a Louisiana law that had made
consensual oral and anal sex a felony in the state. In other words:
my trip to New Orleans is back on!''
</P>
<P>
   ``Jim J. Bullock was arrested in West Hollywood for possession
of the illegal drug crystal meth. He was released on $10,000 bond
and now faces up to two years in prison, although there's talk his
lawyer might plea bargain it up to four years.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Olivia D'Abo, the big sister on the `Wonder Years,' will play
Neve Campbell's love interest on three episodes of `Party of Five,'
when Campbell's character, Julia, enters into a lesbian affair.
That night, I'm gonna be having a little party of five.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; `Bull Sale` &LR;
</P>
<P>
   This couple goes to an agricultural show way out in the
countryside on a fine Sunday afternoon, and are watching the
auctioning off of reproduction bulls. The guy selling the bulls
announces the first bull to be auctioned off: A fine specimen, this
bull reproduced 60 times last year.
</P>
<P>
   The wife nudges her husband in the ribs, and comments: See! That
was more than 5 times a month!
</P>
<P>
   The second bull is to be sold: Another fine specimen, this
wonder reproduced 120 times last year.
</P>
<P>
   Again the wife bugs her husband: Hey, that's some 10 times a
month. What do YOU say to that?!
</P>
<P>
   Her husband is getting really annoyed with this comparison...
The third bull is up for sale: And this extraordinary specimen
reproduced 360 times last year! The wife slaps her husband on the
arm and yells: That's once a day, every day of the year! How about
YOU?!
</P>
<P>
   The husband was pretty irritated by now, and yells back: Sure,
once a day! But ask the announcer if they were all with the same
cow!!!.
</P>
