blindfolded for nearly seven years. (Early summary by wires.) By
Dirk Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   NURSES-SHORTAGE (Washington) The nation's hospitals are
experiencing a shortage of registered nurses, the specialized,
highly trained nurses who manage and staff operating rooms,
emergency rooms, intensive care units and pediatric wards for
high-risk babies. Driven in part by the turmoil and cost-cutting of
managed care, the shortage began a year ago in California and this
year it has touched nearly all acute care hospitals. By Peter T.
Kilborn.
</P>
