<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Tuesday, March 23, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact William Toren at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   MONICA-SIGNING (Los Angeles) _ Monica Lewinsky, fresh from her
Hollywood debut at Vanity Fair's post-Oscar party, signed copies of
``Monica's Story'' at the Century City Shopping Center in what's
been billed as her only U.S. bookstore appearance. By Steve Carney.
(Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTHY-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Convenience store owner Mike
Motazedi took pity on a homeless man who hung out around his store,
gave him the night manager's job and even helped him get an
apartment. But three months into his new job, the man Motazedi
helped emptied the cash drawer, helped himself to cartons of
cigarettes and cases of beer, shoved it all into a duffle and flew
the coop _ leaving the store unmanned for hours allowing would-be
customers to take much of what he left behind, police say. By
Dennis McCarthy. (Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a''
national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   STABBING-TRIAL (Los Angeles) _ After watching a panhandling
transient stab his son stabbed to death on a downtown Los Angeles
street last year, Souren Mekhrabian finds himself being
cross-examined on the witness stand by the man accused of the
killing, who is representing himself at trial. By Donna Huffaker.
(Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
