   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; MONEY PACKAGE &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; TRAVEL _  &LR; Confounding the experts, the nation's airlines have
turned into the 800-pound gorillas of the Internet travel industry.
</P>
<P>
   Their share of online travel bookings soared from 20 percent in
1996 to 50 percent last year and is expected to exceed 60 percent
of the rapidly growing market three years from now. By Arthur M.
Louis
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MONEYBAG &LR;  _ (column) Question: I contribute at work to a 401(k)
plan that is invested in fixed-income securities. I am thinking
about leaving to join another company, and I would like to take the
money with me. I don't plan to touch the money. I only want to roll
it over into an individual retirement account and invest it in
stocks in hopes of getting a better return. Am I allowed to do
