 For Release TUESDAY AMs, March 23, 1999
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Al Simons  &LR; at the Boston
Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics or
photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   POPE-ISRAEL (Jerusalem) _ Pope John Paul will visit the Holy
Land next March to mark the start of Christianity's third
millennium, the Israeli Tourism Ministry said By Charles M.
Sennott. 100.
</P>
<P>
   IRISH-RELEASE (London) _ British home secretary holds up release
of three IRA prisoners in what is seen as a signal to IRA that it
must make a gesture on giving up arms. By Kevin Cullen. 90
</P>
<P>
   PRIMAKOV-VISIT (Moscow) _ Kosovo will top the agenda as Russian
prime minister visits Washington. By David Filipov. 90.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-KOSOVO (Washington) _ The prospect of casualties and
lack of a clear outcome mean Kosovo could spell the end of
President Clinton's luck on foreign policy. Clinton says allies
behind US on strikes. By Ann Scales. 90
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   NEWYORK-POLICE (New York) _ Police shooting of immigrant Amadou
Diallo touched off a sequence of events that have brought in
federal investigators, helped build the stature of Al Sharpton and
revealed the tone-deafness of Rudy Giuliani. By Fred Kaplan. 100.
</P>
<P>
   LEWINSKY-BOOK (Los Angeles) _ The world's most famous intern
visits Los Angeles for what's billed as her only book-signing
appearance in the US. By Lynda Gorov. 90.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   COMCAST-MEDIAONE (Undated) _ Cable giant Comcast to acquire
MediaOne. By Ronald Rosenberg. 80.
</P>
<P>
   RODMAN-CONVERSE (Undated) _ Converse cancels sneaker deal of
unpredictable rebound star Dennis Rodman. By Greg Krupa. 70.
</P>
