<HEADLINE>
SPRING TRAINING 
</HEADLINE>
  (lh) 
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The baseball shirt _ sans team logo _ is shaping up as the
preferred T-shirt for spring. Stella McCartney put airbrushed
designs of birds, palm trees and sunsets on her shirts for Chloe,
but most have solid-color bodies and contrasting sleeves.
</P>
<P>
   Bergdorf Goodman has two styles of the Chloe shirts in white
cotton, one with an eagle on the front and one with smaller birds
($120 each).
</P>
<P>
   The Gap's baseball T's come in white cotton with red, yellow,
green or gray sleeves ($22). At Bloomingdale's the shirts come in
white cotton with pink sleeves or in gray with navy ($24).
</P>
<P>
   Barneys New York has cashmere baseball shirts by Katayone Adeli
in gray with blue sleeves ($195), polyester by Daryl K in white
with blue, gray or black ($130), by Theory in white with gray ($98)
and by Skimpiez in black with gray or in white with pink, red, navy
or light blue sleeves ($42).
</P>
</TEXT>
